{"PENGUIN":[{"def":"Any bird of the order Impennes, or Ptilopteri.","pos":""},{"def":"The egg-shaped fleshy fruit of a West Indian plant (Bromelia Pinguin) of the Pineapple family; also, the plant itself, which has rigid, pointed, and spiny-toothed leaves, and is used for hedges.","pos":""}],"PENGUINERY":[{"def":"A breeding place, or rookery, of penguins.","pos":""}]}